### Replace Zod `errorMap` with function `error` parameter

Source: https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/blob/main/packages/docs/content/v4/index.mdx

Demonstrates the migration from Zod 3's `errorMap` to the unified function-based `error` parameter in Zod 4. This new `error` parameter simplifies complex error customization logic by providing direct access to the validation `issue`.

```typescript
// Zod 3 
z.string({
  errorMap: (issue, ctx) => {
    if (issue.code === "too_small") {
      return { message: `Value must be >${issue.minimum}` };
    }
    return { message: ctx.defaultError };
  }
});
```

```typescript
// Zod 4
z.string({
  error: (issue) => {
    if (issue.code === "too_small") {
      return `Value must be >${issue.minimum}`
    }
  }
});
```

