### Use Zod `.overwrite()` for type-preserving transformations

Source: https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/blob/main/packages/docs/content/v4/index.mdx

Introduces Zod 4's new `.overwrite()` method, which performs transformations without changing the inferred type of the schema. Unlike `.transform()`, `.overwrite()` returns an instance of the original schema class, making the output type introspectable and compatible with tools like JSON Schema generation. The function is stored as a refinement, ensuring type preservation.

```typescript
const Squared = z.number().transform(val => val ** 2);
// => ZodPipe<ZodNumber, ZodTransform>
```

```typescript
z.number().overwrite(val => val ** 2).max(100);
// => ZodNumber
```

