### Unavailable Zod Transformer Syntax in Zod 3

Source: https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/blob/main/packages/docs-v3/MIGRATION.md

This code block illustrates the old transformer syntax from Zod 2 that is no longer supported in Zod 3. Previously, transformers required an input schema, an output schema, and a transformation function. This syntax has been deprecated due to the new `.transform()` method available directly on all Zod schemas.

```typescript
# not available
z.transformer(A, B, func);
A.transform(B, func)
```

