### Chain Zod Methods and `transform` in Correct Order in TypeScript

Source: https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/blob/main/packages/docs-v3/README.md

Emphasizes the importance of chaining order when using `transform` with other Zod methods. Built-in validation methods (like `.email()`) should be applied before `transform` methods, as `transform` changes the schema instance to a `ZodEffects` type, which might not have the original schema's methods.

```ts
const emailToDomain = z
  .string()
  .email()
  .transform((val) => val.split("@")[1]);

emailToDomain.parse("colinhacks@example.com"); // => example.com
```

