### Zod Object Schema `additionalProperties` in Input Mode

Source: https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/blob/main/packages/docs/content/json-schema.mdx

This snippet shows how the `additionalProperties` behavior changes when converting a Zod object schema to JSON Schema in 'input' mode. In this mode, `additionalProperties` is not explicitly set, allowing for additional properties in the input data, unlike the default behavior.

```typescript
import * as z from "zod";

const schema = z.object({
  name: z.string(),
  age: z.number()
});

z.toJSONSchema(schema, { io: "input" });
// => {
//   type: 'object',
//   properties: { name: { type: 'string' }, age: { type: 'number' } },
//   required: [ 'name', 'age' ],
// }
```

