### Validate Specific IP Versions (IPv4/IPv6) with Zod

Source: https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/blob/main/packages/docs-v3/README.md

Demonstrates how to enforce a specific IP version (IPv4 or IPv6) using the `version` option in `z.string().ip()`. It shows how to create schemas for `v4` and `v6` and provides examples of valid and invalid parses for each.

```typescript
const ipv4 = z.string().ip({ version: "v4" });
ipv4.parse("84d5:51a0:9114:1855:4cfa:f2d7:1f12:7003"); // fail

const ipv6 = z.string().ip({ version: "v6" });
ipv6.parse("192.168.1.1"); // fail
```

