### Apply Basic String Transformations in Zod

Source: https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/blob/main/packages/docs/content/api.mdx

This snippet showcases Zod's built-in methods for performing common string transformations. These include trimming whitespace, changing the case of characters (to lower or upper), and normalizing Unicode characters.

```ts
z.string().trim(); // trim whitespace
z.string().toLowerCase(); // toLowerCase
z.string().toUpperCase(); // toUpperCase
z.string().normalize(); // normalize unicode characters
```

```ts
z.string().check(z.trim()); // trim whitespace
z.string().check(z.toLowerCase()); // toLowerCase
z.string().check(z.toUpperCase()); // toUpperCase
z.string().check(z.normalize()); // normalize unicode characters
```

