### Enforce Non-Empty Zod Array with .nonempty()

Source: https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/blob/main/packages/docs-v3/README.md

Explains how to use the `.nonempty()` method to ensure a Zod array contains at least one element. This method also changes the inferred TypeScript type of the array and throws an error if an empty array is parsed.

```ts
const nonEmptyStrings = z.string().array().nonempty();
// the inferred type is now
// [string, ...string[]]

nonEmptyStrings.parse([]); // throws: "Array cannot be empty"
nonEmptyStrings.parse(["Ariana Grande"]); // passes
```

