### Zod Refinement Preventing Execution on Unrelated Error

Source: https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/blob/main/packages/docs/content/api.mdx

This example showcases a common issue where a schema-level refinement, like a password confirmation check, is implicitly skipped if an error occurs in an unrelated field within the same object. It highlights how initial validation failures can prevent subsequent, independent refinements from running in both Zod and Zod Mini.

```ts
const schema = z
  .object({
    password: z.string().min(8),
    confirmPassword: z.string(),
    anotherField: z.string(),
  })
  .refine((data) => data.password === data.confirmPassword, {
    message: "Passwords do not match",
    path: ["confirmPassword"],
  });

schema.parse({
  password: "asdf",
  confirmPassword: "asdf",
  anotherField: 1234 // ❌ this error will prevent the password check from running
});
```

```ts
const schema = z
  .object({
    password: z.string().check(z.minLength(8)),
    confirmPassword: z.string(),
    anotherField: z.string(),
  })
  .check(z.refine((data) => data.password === data.confirmPassword, {
    message: "Passwords do not match",
    path: ["confirmPassword"],
  }));

schema.parse({
  password: "asdf",
  confirmPassword: "asdf",
  anotherField: 1234 // ❌ this error will prevent the password check from running
});
```

